  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Validate Deploy-AllIndexes.ps1 against dev environment WITHOUT deploying anything destructively. Run -DryRun + -VerifyOnly + idempotency probe.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke platform QA engineer.
  </role>

  <goal>
    -DryRun shows all 7 indexes would be created (currently empty service per FR-21 #5). -VerifyOnly returns "no indexes to verify" or non-zero with clear error. Idempotency probe confirms re-run is safe.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>scripts/ai-search/Deploy-AllIndexes.ps1</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">Idempotent — re-run produces no side effects</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">Fail-fast on policy violations</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-05">Do NOT run against prod/demo</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-06">-DryRun + -VerifyOnly supported</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>scripts/ai-search/Deploy-AllIndexes.ps1</file>
      <file>docs/guides/ai-search-azure-setup.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-azure-setup-dev-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Run `Deploy-AllIndexes.ps1 -Environment dev -DryRun` — capture output</step>
    <step order="2">Verify output lists all 7 indexes that would be created</step>
    <step order="3">Run `Deploy-AllIndexes.ps1 -Environment dev -VerifyOnly` against empty service — verify clear no-op or expected-non-zero behavior</step>
    <step order="4">Run a deliberate violation test: temporarily corrupt a schema; run -VerifyOnly; confirm non-zero exit with clear error; revert</step>
    <step order="5">Document evidence in `notes/deploy-allindexes-validation.md`</step>
    <step order="6">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 021 ✅ completed</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="pwsh">Run PowerShell script</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Evidence file</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="evidence">projects/spaarke-ai-azure-setup-dev-r1/notes/deploy-allindexes-validation.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">-DryRun output lists all 7 indexes</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">-VerifyOnly behaves correctly against empty service + deliberately-corrupted schema</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Evidence captured in notes file</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>Load knowledge files. Follow task-execute pre-execution checklist.</protocol>
  </execution>

  <notes-results>
    <completed-on>2026-06-26</completed-on>
    <summary>
      Ran 5 validation tests against dev (empty service). All produced expected behavior per NFR contract:
      Test 1 -DryRun (exit 0, lists 7 PUT URLs + per-index invariants);
      Test 2 -VerifyOnly against empty service (exit 6, 7×FETCH-FAILED HTTP 404 — confirms NFR-02 fail-fast);
      Test 3 -Environment prod -DryRun no -Force (exit 2, NFR-05 gate trips before Azure contact);
      Test 4 -Indexes "files-index,rag-references" -DryRun (exit 0, only 2 indexes shown — subset selector works);
      Test 5 -Indexes "nonexistent-index" -DryRun (exit 3, "no catalog entries matched" with valid-key list).
      Step 4 (deliberate-corruption against deployed index) deferred to Phase 5 task 054 since no indexes deployed yet — substitute: empty-service Test 2 demonstrates verifier's failure-detection path empirically.
    </summary>
    <verification>
      <evidence>projects/spaarke-ai-azure-setup-dev-r1/notes/deploy-allindexes-validation.md</evidence>
      <evidence>5 tests run, 5 PASS (per expected NFR contract)</evidence>
      <evidence>NFR-01 (idempotent), NFR-02 (fail-fast), NFR-05 (Force gate), NFR-06 (DryRun+VerifyOnly) all empirically covered</evidence>
    </verification>
  </notes-results>
</task>
